American talk-show host Wendy Williams' wax figure to be on display at the Madame Tussauds' New York wax museum was revealed on her show recently. On a snap posted on her Instagram, Williams said she was excited for the honour. “Another historic day in Wendy History. I’m so excited to be part of @madametussaudsusa and glad that my son was with me on such a special day,” she said. Other stars with wax figures from the museum include Beyoncé Knowles-Carter, Pharrell Williams, Kylie Jenner and Ed Sheeran.